.TH NHOPKG 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhopkg \- universal package manager for GNU/Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhopkg
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIPACKAGE...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nhopkg
is a universal package manager that works on any GNU/Linux distribution.
It supports binary packages (`.nho`) and source packages (`.srcnho`).
.PP
Packages can be installed locally or fetched from remote repositories.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-install
Install a local binary package (`.nho`).
.TP
.B \-S, \-\-super-install, \-d, \-\-dios
Install a package from configured repository.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-build
Build and install a source package (`.srcnho`).
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-remove
Remove an installed package.
.TP
.B \-\-purge
Also remove packages that depend on the one being removed.
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-list
List all installed packages.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-info
Show detailed information about a package.
.TP
.B \-w, \-\-show
List files contained in a package.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-search
Search for packages in the repository.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-list-repo
List all packages available in the repository.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-create-source
Launch interactive wizard to create a `.srcnho` package.
.TP
.B \-A, \-\-auto-package
Automatically create a `.srcnho` package from a tarball.
.TP
.B \-z, \-\-tgz2nho
Convert a Slackware `.tgz` package to `.nho`.
.TP
.B \-g, \-\-create-repo
Create a local repository from `.nho` files in a directory.
.TP
.B \-U, \-\-update
Update local repository metadata.
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-update-db
Update the internal file database used for dependency resolution.
.TP
.B \-x, \-\-update-shooters
Run system-wide cache updates (icons, MIME, schemas, fonts, etc.).
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-clean
Clear download and build caches.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show this help.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-root=DIR
Install package into an alternate root directory.
.TP
.B \-R, \-\-recursive
Do not prompt for confirmation; answer "yes" automatically.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-deps
Skip dependency checking.
.TP
.B \-\-force-check-deps
Force dependency checking (default behavior).
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-arch
Skip architecture verification.
.TP
.B \-\-no-check-sha256
Skip SHA256 checksum verification.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output=DIR
Write logs or output to specified directory.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/nhopkg/nhopkg.conf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/nhopkg/packages/
Database of installed packages.
.TP
.I /var/lib/nhopkg/files/
List of files installed by each package (compressed).
.TP
.I /var/cache/nhopkg/
Downloaded packages and temporary files.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg.conf (5)
